<item>
            <title>[OAK-3419] ClusterNodeInfo.createInstance fails to clean up random entries</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-3419</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;            &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; mId = &quot;&quot; + doc.get(MACHINE_ID_KEY);
            &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; iId = &quot;&quot; + doc.get(INSTANCE_ID_KEY);
            &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (machineId.startsWith(RANDOM_PREFIX)) {
                &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// remove expired entries with random keys
&lt;/span&gt;                store.remove(Collection.CLUSTER_NODES, key);
                &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;continue&lt;/span&gt;;
            }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The intent seems to be to cleanup entries in the cluster node table that start with RANDOM_PREFIX. However, &lt;tt&gt;machineId&lt;/tt&gt; is checked instead of &lt;tt&gt;mId&lt;/tt&gt;. When &lt;tt&gt;createInstance&lt;/tt&gt; is called with a random id, the whole table might get wiped out. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
